  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How did you get into IIM?",
  "response": "Getting into an Indian Institute of Management (IIM) typically involves a rigorous selection process that includes several stages. Here\u2019s a step-by-step overview of how one might secure admission to an IIM:\n\n### 1. **Eligibility Criteria**\n   - **Educational Qualification**: Candidates must hold a bachelor's degree in any discipline from a recognized university. The minimum percentage required can vary between IIMs, but generally, it is around **50% for General category** and **45% for SC/ST/PwD candidates**.\n   - **Final Year Students**: Those in their final year of graduation can also apply, provided they complete their degree by the specified deadline.\n\n### 2. **Appear for CAT (Common Admission Test)**\n   - The **CAT** is a highly competitive national-level entrance exam conducted by one of the IIMs on a rotational basis.\n   - The exam tests candidates on **Quantitative Ability (QA)**, **Data Interpretation & Logical Reasoning (DILR)**, and **Verbal Ability & Reading Comprehension (VARC)**.\n   - A high percentile (usually **95+**) is required to be considered for shortlisting by top IIMs.\n\n### 3. **Shortlisting for Written Ability Test (WAT) & Personal Interview (PI)**\n   - Based on CAT scores, IIMs shortlist candidates for the next stage, which typically includes:\n     - **Written Ability Test (WAT)**: Candidates are asked to write an essay or express their views on a given topic.\n     - **Personal Interview (PI)**: Candidates are interviewed by a panel to assess their personality, communication skills, and suitability for the MBA program.\n   - Some IIMs may also consider past academic performance, work experience, and diversity factors during shortlisting.\n\n### 4. **Final Selection**\n   - IIMs calculate a composite score based on:\n     - CAT performance\n     - WAT/PI performance\n     - Academic record\n     - Work experience (if applicable)\n     - Diversity factors (gender, academic background, etc.)\n   - Final admission offers are made based on this composite score.\n\n### 5. **Acceptance and Joining**\n   - Selected candidates must confirm their acceptance by paying the required fees and completing formalities.\n   - Once admitted, students join the program at the respective IIM.\n\n### Tips for Success:\n   - **Prepare Thoroughly for CAT**: Focus on accuracy, speed, and time management. Use mock tests and previous year papers for practice.\n   - **Work on Soft Skills**: Develop strong communication and critical thinking skills for WAT and PI.\n   - **Highlight Achievements**: Showcase academic excellence, extracurricular activities, and work experience during the selection process.\n   - **Stay Updated**: Be aware of current affairs and business trends to perform well in WAT and PI.\n\nSecuring admission to an IIM requires hard work, dedication, and a strategic approach. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
